This paper discusses the security and trust issues in anonymous communication over Tor, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper proposes a system that uses Bayesian Belief Networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The system also involves the use of formal language and ontology, which are related to semantic web (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS).
